The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Thursday, November 07, 2002 				 Ambar, Sourav corner Assam 
 BY A STAFF REPORTER 																								Calcutta: Fine bowling by Ambar Roy and Sourav Sarkar helped Bengal gain an upper hand against Assam in the under-19 Cooch Behar Trophy, being played in Cuttack. 																								According to information recieved here, Ambar took five for 37,while Sourav claimed three for 56. Assam were all out for 146. In reply, Bengal finished the opening day on 86 for four. 																								Brief scores: Assam 146 (Ambar Roy 5/37, Sourav Sarkar 3/56). Bengal 86/4. Match to continue. 																								Captains knock 																								In the under-15 Polly Umrigar Trophy too, Bengal tightened their noose around Assam at the Rajdanga ground. 																								On Day II, Bengal declared their first innings on 264 for eight, taking a lead of 132 runs. Rohan Banerjee played a captains knock of 86.																								Brief scores: Assam 132. Bengal 264/8 decl (Rohan Banerjee 86, Srivats Goswami 44 n.o.). Assam 70/4. Match to continue. 
